{
  "doc_id": "15227",
  "text": "With the advent of large data, there has been more opportunity to explore this multi-layer structure. There has been some work in the modeling and representation of multi-layer networks, and how it relates to other studied problems [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . While there is a large body of work in single-layer community detection [CITATION_3] , the multi-layer community detection literature is less comprehensive. Hypergraphs have been studied from a spectral perspective [CITATION_4] , which can be useful when dealing with a multi-layer structure. Some work in applying single-layer modularity methods to multi-layer structures is also available [CITATION_5] . For more information, see [CITATION_6] . This technique was also used in [CITATION_7] .",
